Installation and Configuraiton of Apche-Tomcat on AWS ec2 Instance

Pre-req:
1. java 1.8
2. Set java home path 

Steps:
1.Install java1.8 JDK
yum install java-1.8.0-openjdk
2. Set java home path.

3. Create tomcat user, group and dirrectories.
groupadd tomcat
useradd -g tomcat -d /opt/tomcat -s /bin/nologin tomcat
mkdir -p /opt/tomcat

4. Download the desired tomcat version to ec2 instance, in this case it is - "apache-tomcat-8.5.32"
wget http://www-us.apache.org/dist/tomcat/tomcat-8/v8.5.32/bin/apache-tomcat-8.5.32.tar.gz

5. Unzip and untar the downloaded file. 
tar -zxvf apache-tomcat*tar.gz
mv apache-tomcat-8.5.32/* /opt/tomcat/

6. set the ownership
chown -R tomcat:tomcat /opt/tomcat/

7. move the contents of dir apache-tomcat-8.5.32 to newly created /opt/tomcat
mv apache-tomcat-8.5.32/* /opt/tomcat/

8.




